reviews.text: The worst Panda that i have ever had. The cooks are not real cooks. The food is always burnt. And the super greens have zero flavor, and are barely cooked all the way through. This place scams on the portions, but try to charge you crazy prices. I told the manager that all of my food was burnt and he brushed it off. The menu doesn't even have all of the original items that most panda expresses have. Do not waste the energy, time, or money with this place.

Online closing times are accurate but in-store signage says they close at 6pm.

Please consider updating for those that do not check their phones every time, or perhaps are from out of town and weren't aware you have been closing at "4 for over a year". We came in to shop thinking we could grab food afterwards only to show up at 4:23 to a closed shop.
Rough 5 days in hospital with family.  Didn't eat for most those days and this hit the spot.  Everything was great except the noodles.  Straight up the noodles were super dry.

Place is good and clean. Food was really good but unfortunately the cashier lady👎.
I usually don’t write reviews but this was the 2nd time eating here and same person with not so good attitude.
I’ve never seen a place that delights so much in turning away patrons that show up close to or after closing time.

We stopped by for lunch this past weekend and it was a good experience. The food was good, they definitely could use more seasoning on their burgers, but it wasn’t terrible. Stay away from the Mac and cheeses, it’s just not good. The brussel sprouts however where immaculate! The drinks are also pretty good. Our bartender was nice and attentive even though she had several customers. We also went upstairs to play a game of pool. You have to leave your license or some form of ID with the bartender, then they give you the balls and you get your stick from the pool area
upstairs. At least that’s what happened when we went. There was no bartender working upstairs, so you’ll have to go downstairs if you want a drink. This is a pretty good restaurant all things considered. They can definitely improve on some things, but we would definitely return.

Stopped by for happy hour with coworkers. The drinks were good, and all were $2 off. I also had the chipotle bbq wings and the sweet smokey wings. They were saucy and flavorful. I liked the sweet smokey wings best—they had a bit of a spicy kick to them. The service was attentive, quick and welcoming. The location of the restaurant could not be better.

So many good things about Rock Bottom now, the latest being their new menu with basically a doubling of excellent vegan and vegetarian options. And to whatever extent they've helped keep the street in front blocked to car traffic, with planned music on Fridays and buskers at other times, well major kudos! And the beer, oh the beer!!! And the export stout always there to fill my growler with. And a large meeting/party room for special occasions, pool tables,  excellent decor, and very polite and professional staff.

reviews.author_name: CC's Fitness Hour Lets Motivate To Lose Some Weight
reviews.text:
Food was amazing. From the bison burger, to the sweet smoked wings and then the mac & cheese 😍🔥
Was all delicious. Had a mojito. That was good as well. Joe the Bartender had excellent service as well. Thanks for a good time!

It's not an "avoid at all costs," but please don't come here if you have other options. This place has really declined in food quality and quality control.

The Food

The menu says the 2am burger has hasbrowns, but they replaced it with waffle fries inside the burger inside.
We ordered two burgers with waffle fries and one of the fries was absolutely cold/stale and the other one was crunchy and hot. Burger was decent.

The nachos were stale and cold and was mentioned that it would be for the table as an appetizer. They came out with our mains and we also found a piece of a rubber band shown in the photos.

The flatbread was warm, basically all the food came out at a few degrees above room temp. Maybe they finished all the food and the last thing was the salad so the other food just sat while salad was being worked on.

Service was slow, from getting taking our order to getting the food and this may have been bc we were on the patio. I'm just sad  but mainly disappointed in myself for expecting something else. Please avoid if you can but if you don't, don't expect anything you would ever order twice.

My relatives came into town and they’re vegan, so I decided to give this place a try! I placed a phone order for 3 dishes! All dishes I ordered were really good! Veggie fried rice, vegan lo mein and broccoli oyster dish! Took 10 mins to prep! Really nice worker.

ordered Vegetable Chow Mein, but there were no noodles, just only vegetables!

Additional
Again on 12/15/22, ordered delivery.
Ordered Roast Pork Chow Mein but no noodles in it. What is going on, this is the second time!
Bad customer service and bad food (chicken taste like rubber). Try to charge me for soy source/ hot sauce. Food taste really bad and NOT tasty at all. Expensive too. Don’t go here. Stay away.

Ordered Chicken Curry and barely 1/3 of the bowl is chicken, with a mountain of onion ontop and underneath. Also ordered some shrimp toast and it was burned but the middle was undercooked and mushy. When i called to order the lady answered with “what” and had an attitude while taking my order.

This is my second time ordering from here, i ordered kung pao chicken last time and my bowl again was more celery and peanuts with barely any chicken at all.

The bowls look like theyre prepaired in advance and then just put in a microwave.

All in all terrible. Wouldn’t recommend. 🙅🏽‍♂️

Decent takeout or delivery Chinese food.  Price is o.k. Food came out as ordered.  Rice was stuffed into the box, always a good sign.  Dishes were seasoned, looked and tasted pretty good.  Will make it a point to try other dishes.  Recommend if in the mood for some Chinese food.

Went here for my birthday dinner. I received a $30 birthday certificate in my email. I sat at the bar & was serviced immediately. I ordered the shrimp lovers roll to start off. I had the blue ocean drink which was a great cocktail. I ordered the hibachi shrimp entree. Everything was delicious.

Benihana was a birthday treat for my husband birthday. The customer service experience was beyond amazing! This would’ve been our first time going to a place like Benihana. The Miso soup was amazing along w/ the salad they provided us.

We ordered…
- Steak
- Chicken
- Fried rice with egg
- Zucchini
- Sauce of choice was teriyaki

My husband and I had a lunch date today , it was our first time at this location, we started with a delicious ocean blue , the server Miraf was so nice , the chef Joel did a great job with the food, it was so yummy, we’re definitely coming back ! 👍🏻👍🏻

I go to benihana for my birthday every year for 2 reasons. I like the hibachi cooking experience, and I love food. However, at this location, the one that is in need of improvement is the service staff. While I agree that the cook does a significant amount of the work and dictates the experience, that is not a pass for the service staff to be disengaged or otherwise lazy. I went and waited 20+ minutes for my drink from the bar. I even went to the bar and attempted to pick it up myself only to be told I didn't order (in actually my server didn't order my drink). So, when I finally saw my non-existent server, I inquired about my drink, and he gave me the most *blank* stare. A mess.

The other issues included... telling me the wrong price for a to-go order, waiting 15+ minutes for my ticket, and an absent server. Luckily for me, the one thing they got right was my chef was amazing.

It was great. I haven't been there  over ones year. My family loves Benihana. when my son was 6 or 7 years of age, I remenber him saying...Mommy can we eat at Benihanas everyday? There is my son with now.

Haven’t been here in years but finally came again last night—food & service was just as great as I remembered!  The restaurant has a fancy vibe to it and is dim lit inside.

Food was great!!  For starters, I would recommend the Spinach & Artichoke Dip—it’s creamy and well flavored!  For entrees, I noticed some of the old popular dishes (prime rib, crabcake, etc.) are no longer on the menu, but lots of new items.  There was a “special”, the Arctic Char with Lemon Butter Sauce and Crispy Rock Shrimp ($38)—this was AMAZING!!  The Rotisserie Chicken was good too!  Portions are fairly huge, including the sides.  Cocktail drinks are reasonably priced as well.

Service is excellent here—our server Gabriel was friendly and attentive.  The host or manager comes around to check up on each table too.

Woodmont Grill NEVER disappoints! It's been 3 years+ since I've eaten here and decided to go over the weekend. I ordered the Chesapeake Oysters and the Kale and Rotisserie Chicken Salad absolutely delicious. Kale, picked Rotisserie chicken, herbs and a Honey Lime Vinaigrette. Perfect for lunch, not too heavy however some of the chicken had skin on it. My companion had the Thai Beef Salad with Mango, very tasty. The bartenders, Mikaela and Dillion had outstanding customer service. I will definitely be back soon.

Every dish we ordered was flavorful and with great quality. The crispy oysters had a perfect crunch to each bite and was nicely seasoned. The rotisserie chicken was juicy with all the flavor packed in. The prime fillet was tender and smooth, definitely for steak lovers! However, I would not order the rotisserie chicken again, and would love to try their dover sole (only available on the weekends) next time!

This was a great and positive dining experience. The ambiance is good for a date or a romantic dinner. The wait staff was very attentive and gracious. The host is great, sorry I didn't get her name but she's great. She communicated with patrons who were waiting to make sure the tables were clearing.
I went there for my birthday and really enjoyed everything. My servers name was Jordan and he was great, very pleasant and attentive, I took his suggestions for the entree and it was a good choice.
Elder Collins - better than expected
Rosemary Foccacia - melts in your mouth
The Hawaiian - Everything cooked to perfection

I miss a lot of the old menu however the food is always good and consistent. I have never had bad food here. Drinks are usually on point too. Great service. I truly miss the baked potatoes and wish they would return; I wish a lot of items could return oh well make the best of the tasty items still there.
Great drinks and food! We had a few different drinks, oysters, mussels and scallops. I recommend all! Always a good meal and drink here. Service is never misses too.

On the fine dining side, this restaurant did not disappoint.  Everything was pretty tasty and the wait staff stayed attentive throughout the evening.  We opted to sit outside which had a nice fountain-like display.
The ambiance in the bar area is really cool. We got the shrimp tacos and fried oysters. I liked the tacos better. The oysters were not my favorite. I will go back to try other things.

Ordered two cheeseburgers. They couldn’t add tomato to them, which was surprising but not unheard of. I ordered medium but they ended up on the upper end of medium well, with a very charred outer layer. The garlic aioli was tasteless and the fries were oily and not even as good as McDonald’s fries. Not very impressed, especially considering that these two burgers cost a total of $41 before tip. Pretty disappointed.

Great experience!!! Amazing Oysters, the waiter was so educated about the different Oysters and really took the time to explain what Oysters was best for my pallet..... And the hanger steak was out of this world

The service was prompt and accommodating. We had reservations for eight people and were originally seated in a family area where children were running around and music was playing very loudly. After asking if we could change tables, thankfully they were able to do so. If you have a preference for a quieter area, you may want to ask for it when making the reservation, or they might assume you are fine with sitting in a family area.
The mango margarita I ordered wasn't very good. It was too sweet and arrived warm with ice cubes melting in it... for food I ordered fish tacos, which were excellent. The food was delicious and the presentation was impressive. Everyone at my table loved their food as well. Overall, it was a pleasant place to visit.

Best Mexican Cuisine I have ever tasted!!! Grade A customer service and the food has the most AUTHENTIC taste. Quality vegetables and meats, with outstanding flavor. Seating was spacious and the waitstaff was 2nd to NONE. Food came out hot and fresh, even the chips and salsa was FRESH. I highly recommend if you are craving Mexican flavor, this is the place to GO....

Wonderful atmosphere and the food it's amazing.  Big portions too and not just beautiful presentation but tasteful, not like some places
Our server Carlos was very friendly and make good suggestions and explained very well some of the culinary that we were not used to eat.

Delicious and spicy if you like it that way.  Portions were generous including the guac. Service was terrific, the nacho chips were crispy and light, the dessert sampler was fantastic.  This place prides itself on being in house homemade.  Fresh and worth the trip.

Hey “good looking”! The perfect translation for this wonderful restaurant’s name. How you doing? I finally hit the gold mine as far as Mexican food is concerned. First impression was the salsa and chips. The salsa was so distinctive in its explosive flavors. Wow! The fried calamari and nacho platter were excellent. The calamari melts in your mouth. The nachos were the best I have ever had in my lifetime. I grew up in Istanbul and love street food. To my surprise, the rare delicacy beef tongue tacos were offered. I hit the jackpot! The pork tamales were cooked to perfection. I requested some spicy salsas and was pleasantly surprised when I received the real thing instead of Tabasco. The kitchen here is so professional from the chef to the dishwasher. The Mexican spices were so flavorsome they balanced the taste of our main dishes. Our food arrived nice and hot. Everything was spotless. From the hostess to the waitress and the rest of the dining room staff, they were polite and attentive without being intrusive. We were there on a Monday night and the restaurant was hopping. Our waitress, Diana, and her assistant were on target. All our needs were met - great food and fantastic service. Olé!

We were in Bethesda for the Fine Arts Festival and stopped in at Olazzo for lunch. We had an outside table which was perfect for people watching and soaking up the perfect day. Everyone was very happy with their lunch choices. Shrimp Pesto, Olazzo salad, and Goat Cheese and Walnut salad were all excellent. My vegan brother-in-law had the Spaghetti Alla Checca and was happy, which is not an easy task.
I definitely recommend Olazzo for lunch.

I was tasked with picking a dining spot for a Thursday early dinner with a friend. It was between a Hibachi place and Olazzo, we voted for Olazzo! Glad we did. Food was delicious, our dining experience was made even better by the ambiance of the patio and friendliness of the staff. Oh, and the margarita was the icing on the cake. Speaking of cake, their Tiramisu was just perfect. My friend declared “we’re definitely coming back” as we walked to our cars, full and happy.

Very authentic and delicious Italian restaurant. We started with the signature Olazzo cocktail which was very refreshing. I opted for the sausage and peppers over linguini and was extremely delighted with my choice. The portion was just enough to bring a little home for an evening snack!

Calamari was good. Penne with meatballs were fine. They're made in house. I did expect a different taste but they're alright. Homemade brownie and Gelato were good. The Gelato was the best thing we ate there. Light yet flavourful. Brownie was milk chocolate which we enjoyed. Highlight was eating outside. Love that so many places now have dining outdoors.

The food is really tasty and delicious, not to mention the portion is more than for one person! The vibe and atmosphere is good. The location is pretty and good at the heart of old downtown Bethesda! Above them all it is one of the few places that I see after pandemic they haven’t increased their prices! Highly recommend the place!

I look at a coffee shop as a place to relax, have some coffee and refreshments, read a newspaper or a book, or work with a computer. It's not a nightclub with a DJ playing obnoxious dance music at full volume. But that's what you get at this Starbucks.

Most ridiculous Starbucks I ever visited.  Hired the laziest employees.  Instead of helping customers the gurl was too busy flirting with some random person.  Other employees just stood around and talked to each other.  Left without purchasing.  Really hired the bottom of the barrel at this location.   Disappointing.

Pretty nice place and their collection of music is pretty good. Me and my friend go there to either study or to grab a quick drink while walking around. The service is amazing and pretty quick too depending on how busy they are. The place is really clean as well

Housekeeping was improved since prior visit,  but not the coffee.  Beans had been prematurely harvested and scorched during roasting.  Patrons who enjoy milk, syrup, and other additives in their coffee may well rate Starbucks higher.

Sometimes the barista pulls a bad shot, sometimes they run out of my preferred snack ( oatmeal ) but the staff are all so nice, it's impossible to complain. This truly has neighborhood coffee shop vibes

One of my favorite deli spots in Bethesda great service great food... around the corner from my shop Excellent staff and selection.
As you can see my usual is steak and Cheese... with a Stella 🍺

Wonderful customer service and food. If you are looking for safe gluten free options this is a great spot if your visiting the area. I have celiac and felt safe eating there and also did not get sick. Wish I had this cafe in my local hometown. I would be for sure a return customer weekly.

Ordered Margherita pizza & ordered crab cake entree (both gf). Also ordered gelato later on not pictured.

Cafe also has a great section where you can buy wine and gluten free section (cookies, breads) etc..

Wanted to love it…This place has an old school
charm about it, because it’s a restaurant inside a mom n’ pop corner store. I came here based on the stellar reviews. After dining here I have to be honest and say that I love my food flavorful and delicious, and that is exactly what I expected based on the reviews…

Service was fast, but my kebab, rice, and salad combo left a lot to be desired. The kebab was missing so much authentic flavor, and I was confused by the marinara the kebab were nestled in. The white rice also fell pretty flat. The salad was fresh and I enjoyed the balsamic vinegar dressing.

The dairy and gluten-free cupcakes surprised us, because we honestly aren’t used to having so ma y options. The peanut butter cupcake was solid, but the cookies and cream cupcake was missing so much flavor.

Took advantage of their daily lunch special. As this was a Thursday, I got the turkey Reuben panini. The sandwich was amazing, flavorful and filling. Definitely will return to try the other sandwiches of the day and maybe even the gelato.

5 star review all around. Service, selection and taste.

Walking in and being asked if we would like the GF menu or the conventional menu was an amazing surprise. My family is all gluten free and not having to decipher what we can and cannot eat from the conventional menu was amazing. There is nothing worse than having to tell a child you can have a bun-less hamburger or a green salad.

I would recommend  Lilit Cafe to anyone who is gluten free or not.

name: Bethesda Blues and Jazz Supper Club

reviews.text: We saw Avery Sunshine!! The show was more than amazing. We had great seats. Everything was laid out well. There is a parking garage on the same block as the club and parking is free on the weekends. We showed up at 6p to order food and drinks. The drinks were good. Food was flavored well. They serve the food in take out containers. There is a $20 dollar minimum per person for food/drinks. Overall the atmosphere and experience was a good one. We look forward to seeing more shows here.

Parking can be tricky, especially coming from out of town and not being familiar with the area. Nice location- Bethesda. Love the intimacy of the space. No bad seats. Front tables may even guarantee a spot in the show. Was here for the DC black Broadway production of Grease - my nephew is a cast member. About 10 of us in our party. Didn't order food because we had planned to eat at a local restaurant afterwards. Glad because food seemed to be brought out in plastic containers. A bit disruptive to have wait staff constantly come out during the show asking if we wanted drinks/food. Wait time was too long - one drink came out close to end of show. Not sure if company sets price or venue, but $90@ticket is pricey for local theatre. Website originally said there was a $20 min food order included in ticket when we purchased. That mysteriously disappeared. Would patronize again to offer support to family and friends.

Four stars for a nice venue and a good variety of performers. Good acoustics. Food is ok. Not great, not horrible. Acceptably decent. Drinks are expensive, but I guess that goes with the situation. Staff was nice, friendly and attentive, especially considering the crowd. I was a bit turned off with the bill. A 20% gratuity was added, with a supposedly "custom" tip. The custom part was on top if the already claimed 20%. Regardless, the music was good, and we had fun. Will be back.

This is a nice club to see performers and enjoy an evening out with friends and family. The tables on the main floor are close together so get there early so you don’t have to navigate through so many people. The food and drinks are pretty good and the prices are reasonable. There is stadium styled seating in the back with approximately 8 rows of chairs. You can order drinks and food from the bar area and bring it back to your seat if you sit in the back stadium seats. The sound quality and acoustics of the musical performances is good as well.

I had a good time.  The show started on time. Do not be late.  I was 3 minutes late and the show had started.  The mics were too low for most of the performance and you can hear the people in the lobby,which was very disruptive.  We had to do lots of shhhhhhushing to quiet people down.  If you have to sit in the stadium seating,it was a little tight and hard to eat your food comfortably. Try and get a table if possible or be forewarned. I did enjoy the show and it made up for any irritations.
Have taken 2 type of fries rice and I love the spicy one as it really got the kick . Nice ... too long never have really spicy stuff.

The service was attentive and pleasant. The food was good and portion size was more than adequate. My papaya salad had fresh ingredients. Happy hour ran late here and the wine and beer was all reasonably priced. I would have liked more heat in my food. Also, i missed seeing tile fish on the menu in appetizers.

This place wasn't as expensive as some of the Thai places around the area so thats definitely a plus. Finding free parking can be a challenge on occasion. Server was polite and filled empty glass without being asked. Honestly the Portions were just not that big and the Food was mediocre. It wasn't Bad Just not anything to write/rave about.  If the portions were bigger I'd give this place a 4 instead of 3 because these days just Finding a place with decent food at an acceptable price is hard!

I love pad Thai and this happened to be the closest Thai restaurant near my apartment. Ordered a pad Thai today, it looks like some leftover. There was no fresh bean sprouts, no peanuts, just some smashed noodles and half slice of lime on top. Really disappointed. I still ate it since I was hungry and paid $15 for it. Would not order from here again.

Food/service: I went soon as they opened, so it was nice and quiet, the food came out in a timely manner.
Inside:The dining are was clean.
It was hot outside and warmer inside, the ladies restroom was closed, the mens was nasty and flooding on the floor.
Parking:I went on a weekday and you have to pay for parking.

Best breakfast ever and the coffee was outstanding! So smooth never bitter! Definitely where all the locals eat. Almost everyone who came through the door was greeted by name! Wonderful place! Definitely coming back!!

Classic diner and style of food not often found. Staff is polite and plenty of regulars talking to each other. The food is made to order and comes out quickly. The menu is filled with plenty of choices. Serving portion is large and doubt you’ll leave hungry. Tried. Corned beef has and a breakfast sandwich. Both were good. Plenty of street parking if you don’t get one of the few spots out front.

First time here even though I grew up in the DMV! Came for breakfast on a Saturday at 10 and able to easily get a table. No wait. Service was good and the food was quality. I took my meal home as I couldn’t finish it and it made excellent leftovers. Looking forward to returning.

Man let me tell you THIS is the spot, the guy serving the food at 8am is a clean cut gentleman with a great personality. I ordered the sausage gravy and biscuits with an egg and the man cooked it perfectly. A guy made a special off menu order next to me and the guy had it out in less than 10 minutes. The food was great tasted like back hike food and that's something big coming from a southerner. This is a must visit spot.

Definitely a classic diner with great service and good food. Came here on a Sunday morning, and we were sat quickly. I was happy that they were able to accommodate our party with a baby stroller and toddler. The food was good, but with the limited space and seating, the diner felt a little cramped. Luckily, everyone is so kind that it still made for a great experience.

Good restaurant for conversations. Paella is highly recommended! Fresh seafood with well seasoned rice. We ordered an appetizer and it was quite tasty too — the lemon juice made the squid a little sour, just can’t stop to have another one!

Oh Tapas, my good Tapas, where art thee? in  Guardado’s come look for me…

We had the Gambas Al Ajio (sorry no picture here) we ate it too quickly! the brandy adding a nice touch to the fried garlic and olive oil, the grilled salmon on a bed of chopped tomatoes and capers made was done really well, Tilapia in a demi red wine butter sauce, papas fritas—deep fried potatoes with aioli and tomato sauce felt just right and the special of the day, mushrooms stuffed  with Shrimp was indeed special.

In all, great value for money, terrific portions, fresh produce, and a range of paellas and main courses still to try. The Paellas looked especially inviting and that will be our next order… until then a solid 4.5 stars for great food and great service!
My go-to place whenever I crave some paella. They also have great sangria and tapas. Sometimes they have live music during the weekdays.

My first time at Guardado's was great. I arrived in time for happy hour which offers both food and drink options. The sangria was tasty and the martini strong! The stuffed peppers and ceviche on happy hour were delicious and a great value. There were a couple options from the menu that weren't as tasty or not quite as authentic Spanish cuisine as I'd have hoped, but the great service more than made up for it. I'd definitely recommend this to a friend.

We enjoyed the food very much at Guardado's and were able to get a table on a busy weekend night.  The Paella was perfect.  My only wish was that the service was better.  We ate almost our whole meal with nothing to drink and little attention from our servers.

Exquisitely delicious food and good friendly service. We ordered Tandoori scallops and it was cooked to perfection. Squid was good and so was the eggplant. Main courses were the tastiest. Chicken tikka masala was the bomb!! All those spices just blends so well and really tickles your palate. Chicken cilantro was just as good and the lamb was good too but I most likely won’t order it again next time.
Place was almost perfect. It could have used a little bit of music. They were busy but they  also immediately asked for patience and understanding which I thought was really nice of them. Great experience. Will be back!
It was a great surprise to dinner at this restaurant! You learn about the different foods by each region in India.  The Menu is very interesting and well written

Have been here multiple times over the years.  Only once have I had a dry piece of chicken or beef, and tonivht was not that time.  Even in COVID, this restaurant puts out high quality Indian cuisine.

I had a unique dinning experience last night at passage to India restaurant. I was literally taken on a trip to East India.
I recommend if you have a taste for authentic Indian cuisine
Good Service ✅
Very Courteous and Friendly Staff ✅
♿️Wheelchair Accessible Entrance ✅
🚻Restroom✅

Thoughtfully prepared, delicious food. Staff are accommodating and helpful with dietary restrictions, too. Just let them know what you need and they’ll steer you in the right direction. We love the masala and saag options and the yellow dal is wonderful.

Very good sushi, decent prices, lunch specials, they have parking near the restaurant, very tasty and fresh food.
Thank you!
Nothing to write home about but decent. My can of green tea must have been $5.  Sushi was pretty fresh, no off flavors.  Nothing too interesting for their special rolls. Open for take out only.
Ever since I've been visiting my Father-in-law in Chevy Chase, Maki Maki is our go-to for a quick meal. The salmon fried rice has been my absolute favourite.

Maki Maki has takeout sushi in Bethesda. Fresh, generously apportioned, moderately priced, and beautifully prepared.  Our family has enjoyed takeout once or twice a month forever.  We would also eat at M-M before COVID, but still was so convenient to swing by and pick up, it was on our regular take-out rotation.

Terrific sushi standby with all the usual menu suspects. Nothing fancy, but what they offer is delicious, fresh and well presented and portioned. I've probably eaten here 10 times, and I've never had a less than pleasant experience.

i really didn’t like my pizza like idk if by this picture you guys will understand what i mean but 1 i asked for light sauce and its super saucy the opposite of what i asked for. 2 its very under cooked like the cheese is clumpy because its literally not cooked enough… its a yucky taste sorry but i was expecting a good hand tossed pizza since i specified what i wanted but clearly they don’t listen to your instructions.

The pizza maker (not sure if he's the manager) is really friendly and accommodating. My order was a little delayed when I went to pick up but he was able to resolve it in a very professional and thoughtful manner.

The pizza, bread bites and service are not an issue here.  The pizza is usually great and thr service and drivers are usually fast.  It usually is the details, like if I order a certain sauce then I expect that sauce, or if I ask for additional topping.

Driver didn’t follow instructions on contactless delivery.

The tip was left on the porch where the pizza was supposed to be left.

The driver decided to knock on my door and insisted I sign the receipt (which I didn’t write in another tip , the cash was sitting on the porch, where the pizza was supposed to be left)

He decided to knock on my door again after I had already closed and locked it.

Once I opened the door he proceeded to curse me out for not writing in the tip even though I stated I had no more cash on me. Completely disgusting experience with this domino’s. I’ve ordered from he multiple times and this is a first…

Brooklyn Style Pizza was great! I hadn't had pizza in a while and was really craving it. Being from New York and all, I decided on Dominos! Awesome sauce!!!! I loved it and it was delicious. I wish I could have shared it with my daughter, August. Please pray for us. Keep up the great work, Dominos!

What a nice local bakery and pastry shop. The shop is comfy and have a nice relaxing vibe to it. It is a nice place to just sit and study or chat with a friend or loved one.

The average price of all the baled items were around $4, while the pastries sit at $7.50, which is nothing out of the ordinary for a local shop.

The pastries were just right with a good balance of sweet to it, not too much on the sugar, and perfectly full of flavor.

The latte and hot chocolate were good, but I would say the baked items are much more exciting to visit for than the drinks, which I can say compliment it well.

The server was good and quick and definitely a place to come if your in the area.

Cute pastry shop with GORGEOUS cakes... Almost too many to pick from. They look as good as they taste. Macarons, lattes, many non-coffee options including hot tea and hot chocolate, croissants 🥐, coffee, and a featured cake of the day.
Super cute pastry shop. Everything looks amazing. Coffee is good and so are the pastries. Would recommend going here to get some small bites and coffee.

After months of having great experiences with their exceptional croissants, today we had the most beautiful birthday cake! The quality and decoration were beyond our expectations! Thanks for bringing joy and happiness to our little angel’s 6th birthday party in such a short notice!

I asked Tout de sweet if they could prepare a cake for my daughter’s baby shower.  They did a fabulous job as you can see from the pictures.  In fact, the pastry chef took time out of a very busy day to sit down with me and discuss the design of the cake.  The cake became a centerpiece for the shower and beyond its beautiful appearance, it was incredibly delicious!!

I would definitely recommend Tout de sweet to anyone who is looking for a custom cake for a special occasion.

I was excited to see a vegan strawberry crumble on their menu so I decided to get it for takeout. Received a cold, liquid-y hodgepodge of strawberries and nuts which TBH looked like a bunch of frozen strawberries were allowed to thaw out with some walnuts! I was slightly appaled but   more amused than upset by the audacity of this dish pretending to be a crumble. See pictures below for entertainment.

I give this place three stars despite this because I have had decent risotto from them in the past and I am happy that they have an otherwise decent vegan menu. Just stay away from the soggy strawberry nut mixture

This restaurant gave me and my husband the best service we have ever received. We visited on a nice day in the summer so there was outdoor sitting it was a little warm so they made sure our waters were constant filled. They checked on us in a timely manor and after we started to eat the chef came out to see how we were enjoying the food! All the staff were extremely friendly warm and welcoming! They gave us 5 star service! We will definitely be back!! And I would recommend this place to anyone!!

I hosted an engagement party for 20 people at La Panetteria and the experience was AWESOME! I tried booking several other places in the area before finding this gem and the La Panetteria staff made booking, planning, and payment so much easier than the rest. The food was great, my favorites were the zucchini fritters and the prosciutto and arugula pizza. The service and dining area were super welcoming and felt like our own little slice of Italy. Highly recommend, especially for family events.

Have not gone back since the change of ownership until yesterday.  We were pleasantly surprised by the improvements.   The food was great except the beef milanese, it wasn't bad but just not to the same standard of other dishes we ordered.  The veal chops, the risotto dishes and the fried zucchini were excellent.  The services were enthusiastic and the home made after dinner lemoncello was better than what I had in Sorrento Italy.  With the escalating prices and declining services in Bethesda restaurants, this is a great place to have in our neighborhood.  Their prices are fair.

What a terrific meal!  We called on Christmas Eve, and were able to get a take-out order in 20 minutes.  The branzino was generous and perfectly cooked.  The chicken piccata and mushroom risotto were delicious, and the accompanying veggies were first rate.  Highly recommend.

I ordered a meal. I was told it would be $20 dollars. I thought that was weird seeing as what I ordered was marked on the menu as $10. I asked why that was and then was told "okay I'll charge you the $10". I wish I was making this up. I don't know what nonsense they were trying to pull. To top it off the fries were stale and cold, like they were sitting out for a long time before I even ordered.
To the owners/management: this all happened on Sunday Oct 18th 2020. Might want to check in with the employees you had working that afternoon. They are giving your restaurant a bad name.

Customer service was amazing great staff fast food taste like it was made with love i’ve worked at a few pizza chains and never had manny & Olga s being from the Maryland and Washington dc area not once was way to long because when I finally tasted it now I only want it as my go to fast food pizza shop which offered delivery with tasty food great sauce on the pizza great crust with flavor baked to perfection with the right amount of toppings and i always get extra sauce most places don’t listen they did and didn’t miss  pizza was hot and fresh and was so good ate a large myself and ate the last 2 slices the next day 10/10 in my book and i only leave reviews for places even worth it thanks manny & Olgas for a great first time great deals worth every penny only paid 11 for a large with 3 toppings

My wife and I love this place. Our location in Bethesda is a takeout and not a dining location. We live just above the restaurant. It's open really late when we get hungry coming back from vacation and other trips. We have always experienced more than friendly and professional service. We love the food in the variety of food. The presentation is always phenomenal. The delivery men and women are so kind. Thank you Manny and Olga's for being an exceptional business. We love you!

Some of the best pizza I've had in the area. Even if you have to warm up a slice a day later, it still tastes fresh, unlike some of the other big chains that turn into cardboard (Domino's, Papa John's, etc). I would highly recommend this store to others who are new in the area and want good pizza

There’s no 0 rating so I’m forced to click on 1 star. Hubby ordered pizza for delivery and they brought the wrong pizza. He reached out to get it corrected and they said they were sending a new one. Hour later, he called and they said, driver is on the way but the pizza never arrived. NEVER AGAIN!!!
